</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,909,2033]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">
Comments:—According to 
<bibRefCitation author="O'Kelly, C. J. &amp; Yarish, C." box="[525,824,1628,1654]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" pagination="548 - 558" refId="ref8198" refString="O'Kelly, C. J. &amp; Yarish, C. (1980) Observations on marine Chaetophoraceae (Chlorophyta) I. Sporangial ontogeny in the type species of Entocladia and Phaeophila. Journal of Phycology 16: 548 - 558. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1529 - 8817.1980. tb 03073. x" type="journal article" year="1980">O’Kelly &amp; Yarish (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Batters" authorityYear="1902" baseAuthorityName="P. Crouan &amp; H. Crouan" box="[836,1108,1629,1654]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Phaeophilaceae" genus="Phaeophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="dendroides">
<emphasis box="[836,1108,1629,1654]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">Phaeophila dendroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized in terms of the structure and development of its zoosporangia and by the architecture of the flagella apparatus of the zoospore. These characteristics led Chappel 
<emphasis box="[672,730,1705,1730]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
(1990) to consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Batters" authorityYear="1902" baseAuthorityName="P. Crouan &amp; H. Crouan" box="[960,1118,1705,1730]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Phaeophilaceae" genus="Phaeophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="dendroides">
<emphasis box="[960,1118,1705,1730]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">P. dendroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having a well-delimited evolutionary lineage within the 
<taxonomicName box="[523,680,1742,1768]" class="Ulvophyceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="class">Ulvophyceae</taxonomicName>
, and they suggested creating a new family (
<taxonomicName authorityName="D.F.Chappell, C.J.O Kelly, L.W.Wilcox &amp; G.L.Floyd" authorityYear="1990" box="[1192,1378,1742,1768]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Phaeophilaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="family">Phaeophilaceae</taxonomicName>
) and order (Phaeopilales). This proposal was recently supported by 
<bibRefCitation author="O'Kelly, C. J. &amp; Wisor, B. &amp; Bellows, W. K." box="[926,1187,1780,1806]" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" pagination="789 - 799" refId="ref8255" refString="O'Kelly, C. J., Wisor, B. &amp; Bellows, W. K. (2004) Gene sequence diversity and the phylogenetic position of algae assigned to the genera Phaeophila and Ochlochaete (Ulvophyceae, Chlorophyta) Journal of Phycology 40: 789 - 799. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1529 - 8817.2004.03204. x" type="journal article" year="2004">
O’Kelly 
<emphasis box="[1035,1097,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
based on molecular studies which revealed that morphologically indistinguishable specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Batters" authorityYear="1902" baseAuthorityName="P. Crouan &amp; H. Crouan" box="[1101,1267,1818,1843]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Phaeophilaceae" genus="Phaeophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="57" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="dendroides">
<emphasis box="[1101,1267,1818,1843]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="57">P. dendroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from distinct localities were genetically distinct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
